guid":"bN55LJMkQkagp90Tr3m5XA","children":[]},{"id":"301","parent":"298","text":"PRS de TDAH ↑ → peor función ejecutiva en MCI y demencia (Leffa 2025, Alz Dement)","guid":"wjmo9EXsTYGgBuAwSCgGpA","children":[]},{"id":"302","parent":"298","text":"PRS de TDAH ↑ → hipometabolismo FDG-PET frontoparietal","guid":"r51Wiq7nS1OzwzvWNRqcXA","children":[]},{"id":"303","parent":"298","text":"Revisión sistemática → TDAH puede ser FR para demencia, Alzheimer, DLB, DCL (Carr 2024)","guid":"d4BGVr1MStKBgBfSjrCidA","children":[]},{"id":"304","parent":"298","text":"Hipótesis → solapamiento sintomático neurobiológico y factores de riesgo compartidos","guid":"7nJ0jymqToqnpWro0_9mLA","children":[]}]},{"id":"305","parent":"290","text":"Diagnóstico diferencial en >65a","guid":"VFWnC5q3Q9-L0006_V97hQ","children":[{"id":"306","parent":"305","text":"TDAH previo no diagnosticado vs DCL inicial","guid":"FUMAULRAQp-fH0S7dTSD4g","children":[]},{"id":"307","parent":"305","text":"TDAH + depresión vs pseudodemencia","guid":"gSlnpCsASi-CYHThKroKxg","children":[]},{"id":"308","parent":"305","text":"Buscar síntomas desde infancia → criterio rigido","guid":"JF2miBWtRzOK_-g2jrc0Fg","children":[]},{"id":"309","parent":"305","text":"Considerar demandas ambientales y scaffolding","guid":"AnXoR1YwSg2wMpJuXnN3kQ","children":[]},{"id":"310","parent":"305","text":"Evaluar funcionalidad ECOLOGICA (Torralva 2013)","guid":"grCrKvnUTkOP8xiTgtqtJQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"311","parent":"290","text":"Consideraciones farmacológicas","guid":"TjxKstD4T8OHvCeuCIqvdQ","children":[{"id":"312","parent":"311","text":"Farmacocinética alterada en AM → dosis conservadoras","guid":"iWnobNzsTxqPxnkPCFuUtA","children":[]},{"id":"313","parent":"311","text":"Carga anticolinérgica → evitar atomoxetina si polifarmacia","guid":"X4yca7sARfCvrDd3Vd1gQg","children":[]},{"id":"314","parent":"311","text":"Estimulantes → PRECAUCION con HTA arritmias CI","guid":"RLPUcK66T-GWkXoDtyVK-w","children":[]},{"id":"315","parent":"311","text":"α2 agonistas → riesgo hipotensión ortostática y caídas","guid":"pcXGEVPbS3SK4Q2G7URGIA","children":[]},{"id":"316","parent":"311","text":"STOPP-START → revisar al iniciar","guid":"hMpKlpghQgm6jhQ5fujwwQ","children":[]},{"id":"317","parent":"311","text":"Combinar con tratamiento de demencia si coexiste (AChE)","guid":"BslfFn5MRgOJ9BWveXwEnw","children":[]}]},{"id":"318","parent":"290","text":"Evidencia limitada → necesidad de RCTs en población geriátrica","guid":"SsMi18HuS4OF-6o0aAgQ5g","children":[]}]},{"id":"319","parent":"0","text":"Calidad de vida","guid":"e_tTopawSUuXosPo39el4w","children":[{"id":"320","parent":"319","text":"Impactos sistémicos a lo largo de la vida","guid":"CgZ5R3wkQL2qX48no9YH1Q","children":[]},{"id":"321","parent":"319","text":"Niños y adolescentes","guid":"Jz59s7yDQVSZCXyk0MvM2Q","children":[{"id":"322","parent":"321","text":"Fracaso escolar y ocupacional","guid":"TBNSsdecTGG1xwF6xf6cGA","children":[]},{"id":"323","parent":"321","text":"Exclusión social conflictos familiares","guid":"yHzkGwFwSjST10NxRSLJdg","children":[]},{"id":"324","parent":"321","text":"Embarazo adolescente ITS","guid":"iH63dsvBSQOrpK4L2e3mmw","children":[]},{"id":"325","parent":"321","text":"Lesiones accidentales","guid":"10pbymAWSPWHi9-5gqbSLQ","children":[]},{"id":"326","parent":"321","text":"Menor autoestima y bienestar","guid":"x1ydNR0xRQq464VDtdLlxQ","children":[]},{"id":"327","parent":"321","text":"Riesgo suicida aumentado","guid":"NkcT1T0dRoq9jgW8U3XOFg","children":[]}]},{"id":"328","parent":"319","text":"Adultos","guid":"Is7oBx8MQ1KgSPTKRoJyQg","children":[{"id":"329","parent":"328","text":"Disfunción laboral relacional financiera y parental","guid":"EEww4KbSQNmGoFgIRYs9QA","children":[]},{"id":"330","parent":"328","text":"Accidentes vehiculares","guid":"U7kL9Vo9Q9OlDvZGK9-Elg","children":[]},{"id":"331","parent":"328","text":"Enfermedades cardiometabólicas","guid":"FDUl7sETT8WmjNBryNZwXQ","children":[]},{"id":"332","parent":"328","text":"Muerte prematura (Dalsgaard 2015)","guid":"2qYg441nTDevxhqnmvHIFA","children":[]}]},{"id":"333","parent":"319","text":"Tratar TDAH SALVA VIDAS","guid":"01tUm77wTHW5AR02D0lESg","children":[{"id":"334","parent":"333","text":"Medicación ↓ accidentes automovilísticos","guid":"P_ozeH-7RTy4wjHlX4Jh1w","children":[]},{"id":"335","parent":"333","text":"Medicación ↓ TUS","guid":"OQMDsAGHQmqjfeb1offhFA","children":[]},{"id":"336","parent":"333","text":"Medicación ↓ lesiones y fracturas","guid":"iBHMsWpkS0SEU4BwNVvyhw","children":[]},{"id":"337","parent":"333","text":"Medicación ↓ ITS y embarazo adolescente","guid":"Yf7YY2bgQ_-vY9MdPFfpvg","children":[]},{"id":"338","parent":"333","text":"Medicación ↓ depresión y suicidio","guid":"W0oQ2-UFSBqmLuK24ACQFQ","children":[]},{"id":"339","parent":"333","text":"Medicación ↓ criminalidad","guid":"NFZW1igYQGKB1fN0o4XEYA","children":[]},{"id":"340","parent":"333","text":"Medicación ↓ mortalidad general (Vasiliadis 2024, Transl Psychiatry)","guid":"Lya8BCqmRheOoOJE8wrpew","children":[]},{"id":"341","parent":"333","text":"Medicación ↑ retención y logro educacional","guid":"S96ZyprPSEasT_nAmlhscQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"342","parent":"319","text":"Escalas QoL","guid":"_3L0lIdnR9K4F2qEiiLZnQ","children":[{"id":"343","parent":"342","text":"Niños → KIDSCREEN-10 FSI DD-CGAS","guid":"aDqX-_DKTHeSL0uKVy0N3A","children":[]},{"id":"344","parent":"342","text":"Adultos → SF-36 QLESQ AAQoL WFIRS","guid":"6iCsnSj6TtioWBUv6ccvEQ","children":[]},{"id":"345","parent":"342","text":"Chile → MEC-QoL escala propia (González-Hernández 2013)","guid":"Jrmh5uK_RMWniANoNdhiuw","children":[]}]},{"id":"346","parent":"319","text":"CBT agrega mejoría en QoL → meta-análisis","guid":"KdxqRBWqRSihdxsIuyuPXw","children":[]},{"id":"347","parent":"319","text":"Discontinuar medicación → ↓ QoL","guid":"RWkovVx8TKiilgFLZII-1w","children":[]}]},{"id":"348","parent":"0","text":"Perlas clínicas","guid":"Efn59gcuTNKKX1POE2rASg","children":[{"id":"349","parent":"348","text":"70-80% tiene UNA comorbilidad → asumir siempre y tamizar","guid":"G_xre94aQ8iF2IJn5zIuAw","children":[]},{"id":"350","parent":"348","text":"Si no responde a tratamiento óptimo → buscar comorbilidad oculta (ansiedad depresión TUS SAHOS)","guid":"_CBIYWguS9Cv6Gaj089Reg","children":[]},{"id":"351","parent":"348","text":"Diagnóstico es CLINICO → no escaneos ni escalas aisladas","guid":"4rZ5iBp3RF6vEy5gG8aHpw","children":[]},{"id":"352","parent":"348","text":"Tabaquismo materno NO es causa directa → confounding genético","guid":"jFebV5d-SLymJoIsqnJx8A","children":[]},{"id":"353","parent":"348","text":"Estimulantes NO empeoran tics a nivel poblacional","guid":"B6k-gG6MR0yFKzsNL33syA","children":[]},{"id":"354","parent":"348","text":"Estimulantes ↓ mortalidad y accidentes → tratar es salvar vidas","guid":"nk2-Mpu6SFKtzslVfUu1xQ","children":[]},{"id":"355","parent":"348","text":"TDAH adulto \"de inicio\" es raro → buscar síntomas en infancia","guid":"xWzs0kNaS8WNy9iKQYOrJQ","children":[]},{"id":"356","parent":"348","text":"Insomnio y ↓ apetito son manejables → no suspender tratamiento efectivo","guid":"m2bsWknGRde41JITb8NCrA","children":[]},{"id":"357","parent":"348","text":"Mujeres subdiagnosticadas → tamizar en consulta","guid":"AY-7ElnuTCKGiDyEYf4xvw","children":[]},{"id":"358","parent":"348","text":"En adulto mayor → TDAH puede confundirse con DCL incipiente","guid":"iZG2B9MnTDGBR2vLuxoGbg","children":[]},{"id":"359","parent":"348","text":"PRS elevado de TDAH → ↑ riesgo declive cognitivo y Alzheimer","guid":"gzySDXezTAClP78WwQCuCQ","children":[]},{"id":"360","parent":"348","text":"DIVA-5 es gold standard en adulto","guid":"W1D1czwMQkKoHjCvlduEZQ","children":[]},{"id":"361","parent":"348","text":"Escalas de screening ≠ diagnóstico","guid":"yuhWEa5fQJK0wH1S6oejkQ","children":[]},{"id":"362","parent":"348","text":"Psicoeducación es la base de todo plan terapéutico","guid":"lEyc9rvNRFGad6yWa2_grg","children":[]},{"id":"363","parent":"348","text":"Mediterránea y DASH → dietas coadyuvantes razonables","guid":"sw0n3RnGToumizWL9ZMwuA","children":[]},{"id":"364","parent":"348","text":"Ejercicio → recomendar por salud CV más que por síntomas TDAH","guid":"wOdU13wPShukeqLSDLG1Cw","children":[]}]},{"id":"365","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"Qfo0vex2QRax-0wDNihsww","children":[{"id":"366","parent":"365","text":"1. Faraone SV, Bellgrove MA, Brikell I, et al. Attention-deficit/hyperactivity disorder. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2024;10(1):11. doi:10.1038/s41572-024-00495-0","guid":"_4EinXczTmS-emu5m-8Jfg","children":[]},{"id":"367","parent":"365","text":"2. Demontis D, Walters GB, Athanasiadis G, et al. Genome-wide analyses of ADHD identify 27 risk loci. Nat Genet. 2023;55(2):198-208. doi:10.1038/s41588-022-01285-8","guid":"na07KvS8TTWg8h7JyFzsDQ","children":[]},{"id":"368","parent":"365","text":"3. Cortese S, Adamo N, Del Giovane C, et al. Comparative efficacy and tolerability of medications for ADHD: network meta-analysis. Lancet Psychiatry. 2018;5(9):727-738.","guid":"1kX1AHt6Q0u26gp55qHEMw","children":[]},{"id":"369","parent":"365","text":"4. Sonuga-Barke EJS, Brandeis D, Cortese S, et al. Nonpharmacological interventions for ADHD: systematic review and meta-analyses. Am J Psychiatry. 2013;170(3):275-289.","guid":"mhDeft3ARI2ViZ3b5pqr0Q","children":[]},{"id":"370","parent":"365","text":"5. Song P, Zha M, Yang Q, et al. The prevalence of adult ADHD: systematic review and meta-analysis. J Glob Health. 2021;11:04009.","guid":"rDtPB2--Q56rMD5zIbj0yQ","children":[]},{"id":"371","parent":"365","text":"6. Dalsgaard S, Ostergaard SD, Leckman JF, et al. Mortality in children, adolescents, and adults with ADHD: nationwide cohort study. Lancet. 2015;385(9983):2190-2196.","guid":"Fqk0JZQURZW9Ixx0K_3udg","children":[]},{"id":"372","parent":"365","text":"7. Li L, Chang Z, Sun J, et al. ADHD as risk factor for cardiovascular diseases: nationwide population-based cohort study. World Psychiatry. 2022;21(3):452-459.","guid":"-7-4eUXjTn6XnDjhAKJqJA","children":[]},{"id":"373","parent":"365","text":"8. Leffa DT, Ferrari-Souza JP, Bellaver B, et al. Genetic risk for ADHD predicts cognitive decline and AD pathophysiology in cognitively unimpaired older adults. Mol Psychiatry. 2023;28(3):1248-1255. doi:10.1038/s41380-022-01867-2","guid":"hVRsnkfNTeupAxxgi8DC0w","children":[]},{"id":"374","parent":"365","text":"9. Leffa DT, Povala G, Bellaver B, et al. Impact of ADHD polygenic risk scores in Alzheimer disease. Alzheimers Dement. 2025;21(2):e70003. doi:10.1002/alz.70003","guid":"xpJYSj5kQBK3wZQHmL-snQ","children":[]},{"id":"375","parent":"365","text":"10. Carr RH, Eom GD, Brown EE. ADHD as a potential risk factor for dementia and other neurocognitive disorders: systematic review. J Alzheimers Dis. 2024;98(3):773-792. doi:10.3233/JAD-230904","guid":"NTC59feDRq-W79Ras_ryJw","children":[]},{"id":"376","parent":"365","text":"11. Vasiliadis HM, Lunghi C, Rahme E, et al. ADHD medications and risk of mortality and unintentional injuries: population-based cohort study. Transl Psychiatry. 2024;14(1):128. doi:10.1038/s41398-024-02825-y","guid":"4Koc-kVeQfm14jDuEeg71g","children":[]},{"id":"377","parent":"365","text":"12. Torralva T, Gleichgerrcht E, Lischinsky A, et al. Ecological and highly demanding executive tasks detect real-life deficits in high-functioning adult ADHD patients. J Atten Disord. 2013;17(1):11-19.","guid":"_eTLov2RR8uvragrkP2FPA","children":[]},{"id":"378","parent":"365","text":"13. Kooij JJS, Francken MH. DIVA 2.0. Diagnostic Interview for ADHD in adults. DIVA Foundation; 2010.","guid":"tjsVNFvKSe2HIHFNYNXKjQ","children":[]},{"id":"379","parent":"365","text":"14. NICE. Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder: diagnosis and management. NICE guideline NG87. 2019.","guid":"c_ByGc60SG6f-Kl07jvz1Q","children":[]},{"id":"380","parent":"365","text":"15. APA. Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders. 5th ed, Text Revision. American Psychiatric Publishing; 2022.","guid":"NUptr2IDQOK_kJLaGTr_Ng","children":[]},{"id":"381","parent":"365","text"